Here is the package I am offering:

 1. The gun - Glock Model G37 in .45 GAP.  It has had Advantage Tactical Firefly night sights installed by the owner of Advantage Tactical - Richard Nasef. Richard is a former team mate of Jerry Miculek and knows his stuff. He had the grips stippled. I think it is an EXTREMELY good job of that. In the process the gunsmith contoured the thumb rest area of the grip to make it easier to push the mag release without shifting the grip on the pistol. Sort of like what Glock tried to do with the Gen 4, but better in my opinion. I have never felt a Glock this comfortable or this "sticky" in the hand. The stippling doesn't make the gun want to catch clothing like checkering would have. It is a great pistol with zero problems. Oh, the sights come with all the inserts available at Advantage Tactical. This was Richard's personal pistol. If you are a Glock guy, you will love it. It has a 5 pound competition trigger installed as well. This pistol is one year old and has been shot very little. 

 To read about these sights, here is a link. I love them and even have them on a shotgun.

 http://www.advantagetactical.com/

 2. Over 700 rounds of loaded ammunition. It is sorted and labeled. It weighs - I kid you not - right at 30 pounds. I just weighed it and was shocked. All of it is 230 grain, and the majority is hollow point. 

 3. Over 2,000 rounds of once fired brass. Richard had a couple of competition pistols in this caliber. He gave me this brass, and I am of course not charging for it here. Weight? Only a little over 14 pounds of brass!!

 Price is reduced to $500 for all of it. The ammo will come in a separate box of course.  I saw on the major auction site (Gunbroker) where somebody is selling one similar with 700 rounds of ammo. He started his auction at way over $900 and wants over $1000 plus shipping for it. That one is a standard Glock 37 without the extras here. As far as I know it has never been in a holster. It comes with its original Glock case, 5 magazines, the cleaning brush, and the Glock papers/books.

The biggest issue with a .45 GAP is supposedly ammo availability. They have it at all the major gun stores, and even at Walmart. Pricing is about the same as for decent .45 ACP ammunition. At any rate, this package gets rid of most of the problem anyway.

Im fairly firm on the price, so no lowball offers please.
